# Code style

## Formatting (Prettier-enforced)

- 2-space indentation
- Single quotes for strings, double for JSX attributes
- Trailing commas (all)
- 100-char line width
- LF line endings
- `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` sorts Tailwind classes — let it run.

## Naming

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Components | PascalCase | `UserCard.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase, `use` prefix | `useDebounce.ts` |
| Utilities | camelCase | `formatDate.ts` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_RETRIES` |
| Types/Interfaces | PascalCase | `UserProfile` |
| Folders | kebab-case (when multi-word) | `user-profile/` |
| Test files | `*.test.tsx` / `*.test.ts` colocated in `src/test/` |

## Component structure

```tsx
import { type ReactNode } from 'react';

interface CardProps {
  title: string;
  children: ReactNode;
}

export function Card({ title, children }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <div className="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 dark:border-slate-800">
      <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold">{title}</h2>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

- Named export preferred over default (except root `App`).
- `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/aliases.
- Use `type` keyword in imports when type-only: `import { type Foo }`.
- Destructure props in the signature when there are ≥3 props.

## Avoid

- ❌ Inline `style={{}}` (use Tailwind classes)
- ❌ `any` (warning, not error — but prefer `unknown` + type guard)
- ❌ Default exports except for root pages
- ❌ Comments that restate the code
- ❌ Premature abstractions — three similar lines > one helper
- ❌ Empty try/catch — log or re-throw

## Imports

- Absolute paths via TS config (no relative `../../../`)
- Group order: 1) external, 2) internal `@/`, 3) relative `./`
- Newline between groups
- Alphabetical within group (Prettier handles)